Reasoning: The paper discusses various aspects of multicarrier communications, including waveform design, filter design, and practical implementation issues. These topics are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), communication and networking (cs.COMM), systems and control (cs.SY), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and multimedia (cs.MM). However, given the focus on communication systems and signal processing, cs.IT and cs.COMM are the most likely sub-categories. The other sub-categories are also relevant but to a lesser extent.
